tags.name: Eagle Farm
tags.note: The original Eagle Farm railway station opened in 1897 just 90 metres past Airport. It closed in 1977 with the opening of Whinstanes-Doomben station.

tags.name: Eagle Farm
tags.note: Opened in 1952 as Baraini railway station, it was renamed a few months later to Airport railway station. It was renamed Eagle Farm railway station in 1988 along with the electrification of the line, only until a few metres past the station.
